                    <span>A classic in Chinese literature. Arthur Waley is the best translator of  Chinese works that I have found. This version of the Analects are  extensively footnoted which I found broke up the flow of the reading. So I  read it through first without the footnotes, then read it again with them.  A interesting look at Chinese thought at the time.</span>
                  
